The paper deals with wireless sensor networks, communication constraints, and change detection, which are all topics that fall under the information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY) categories. The use of the cumulative sum (CuSum) algorithm and censoring strategies suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.MA) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Finally, the paper involves numerical simulations, which could place it in the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) category.
